<TEI.2><text><body><div1 type="alphabetic letter" n="M" org="uniform" sample="complete"><entryFree key="Mart1" type="main" opt="n"><orth extent="full" opt="n">Mart,</orth> subst. 1) market-place: <bibl n="shak. err 1.2.74" default="NO" valid="yes">Err. I, 2, 74</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. err 2.1.5" default="NO" valid="yes">II, 1, 5</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. err 2.2.6" default="NO" valid="yes">II, 2, 6</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. err 3.2.155" default="NO" valid="yes">III, 2, 155</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. err 3.2.155" default="NO" valid="yes">III, 2, 155</bibl> <cit><quote>you beat me at the m.</quote> <bibl n="shak. err 3.1.12" default="NO" valid="yes">III, 1, 12</bibl></cit>. <cit><quote>I'll meet with you upon the m.</quote> <bibl n="shak. err 1.2.27" default="NO" valid="yes">I, 2, 27</bibl></cit>. <bibl n="shak. err 2.2.166" default="NO" valid="yes">II, 2, 166</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. err 3.1.7" default="NO" valid="yes">III, 1, 7</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. err 5.261.7" default="NO" valid="yes">V, 261</bibl>. <cit><quote>to come so smug upon the m.</quote> <bibl n="shak. mv 3.1.49" default="NO" valid="yes">Merch. III, 1, 49</bibl></cit>.<lb />2) public purchase and sale: <cit><quote>at any Syracusian --s and fairs,</quote> <bibl n="shak. err 1.1.18" default="NO" valid="yes">Err. I, 1, 18</bibl></cit>. <cit><quote>foreign m. for implements of war,</quote> <bibl n="shak. ham 1.1.74" default="NO" valid="yes">Hml. I, 1, 74</bibl></cit>. <cit><quote>we lost too much money this m.</quote> <bibl n="shak. per 4.2.5" default="NO" valid="yes">Per. IV, 2, 5</bibl></cit>.
<lb />3) bargain: <cit><quote>venture on a desperate m.</quote> <bibl n="shak. shr 2.329" default="NO" valid="yes">Shr. II, 329</bibl></cit> (cf. <emph>Co-mart</emph>).
</entryFree></div1></body></text></TEI.2>